    "faq": [
        {
            "question": "What is GyaanSetu?",
            "answer": "GyaanSetu is a comprehensive education platform that combines online courses, live collaborative whiteboards, blockchain-verified certificates, and community features to provide a complete digital learning experience."
        },
        {
            "question": "How do I register as a student?",
            "answer": "Visit the main website, click Sign Up, select Student role, fill in your details including email and password, then complete your profile with academic information like degree, semester, and college name."
        },
        {
            "question": "How do I join a live class?",
            "answer": "Check your dashboard for scheduled classes. Click on a live class to be redirected to the whiteboard. Enter the Room ID provided by your teacher, select Student role, enter your name, and click Join Whiteboard."
        },
        {
            "question": "What courses are available?",
            "answer": "Courses are available in categories: Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, English, Web Development, Designing, AI/ML, and Other. Courses come in multiple difficulty levels (Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced) and languages (English, Hindi, Bengali, Marathi, Kannada, Punjabi)."
        },
        {
            "question": "How are certificates verified?",
            "answer": "Certificates are stored on the Ethereum blockchain. Anyone can verify a certificate by entering the Certificate ID or Hash on the verification page. The system checks the blockchain for authenticity and revocation status."
        },
        {
            "question": "Can I make donations to support education?",
            "answer": "Yes! You can make monetary donations (minimum ₹1) or donate resources like books, electronics, stationery, or furniture. Anonymous donation option is available."
        },
        {
            "question": "What tools are available on the whiteboard?",
            "answer": "The whiteboard includes pencil/freehand drawing, shapes (rectangle, circle, triangle, diamond, star, arrow, pentagon, hexagon, heart, cloud), line tool, text, eraser, color selection, stroke width adjustment, and fill styles."
        },
        {
            "question": "Can I upload PDFs to the whiteboard?",
            "answer": "Yes, teachers can upload PDF files which are automatically converted to slides. Each page becomes a separate slide that can be annotated."
        },
        {
            "question": "Are classes recorded?",
            "answer": "Yes, live classes are automatically recorded. After the session, the recording is uploaded to cloud storage, transcribed using AI, and notes are automatically generated."
